+# Memory Management Architecture Refactoring
+
+## Overview
+
+This document describes the comprehensive refactoring of the gVisor memory management architecture. The refactoring addresses several key issues identified in the original implementation and introduces improvements for better performance, reliability, and observability.
+
+## Changes Summary
+
+### 1. FileMem Decommit Failure Handling (`pkg/sentry/platform/filemem/filemem.go`)
+
+#### Problem
+When `fallocate(FALLOC_FL_PUNCH_HOLE)` fails during memory reclamation, the system falls back to manual zeroing, which doesn't reduce actual memory usage. This can lead to memory bloat over time.
+
+#### Solution
+- **Added decommit statistics tracking**: Track total attempts, failures, and bytes zeroed
+- **Implemented exponential backoff**: Reduce reclaim pressure when consecutive failures occur
+- **Added observability**: `GetDecommitStats()` method to expose decommit metrics
+
+#### Key Changes
+```go
+// New fields in FileMem struct
+decommitFailures uint64
+decommitStats struct {
+    mu             sync.Mutex
+    totalAttempts  uint64
+    totalFailures  uint64
+    totalZeroed    uint64
+    lastFailureMsg string
+}
+```
+
+#### Benefits
+- Better handling of persistent decommit failures
+- Reduced CPU usage during failure scenarios
+- Visibility into memory reclamation health
+
+---
+
+### 2. UpdateUsage Scan Performance Optimization (`pkg/sentry/platform/filemem/filemem.go`)
+
+#### Problem
+`UpdateUsage()` performs full O(n) scans through all memory segments using mincore(), even when only a small portion may have changed. This becomes expensive for large memory spaces.
+
+#### Solution
+- **Incremental dirty tracking**: Track which chunks may have uncommitted pages
+- **Selective scanning**: Only scan dirty chunks when optimization is beneficial
+- **Automatic cleanup**: Clear dirty tracking after successful scans
+
+#### Key Changes
+```go
+// New field in FileMem struct
+usageDirty map[uint64]bool  // Tracks dirty chunks at chunkSize granularity
+
+// New helper functions
+func (f *FileMem) markDirtyRange(fr platform.FileRange)
+func (f *FileMem) clearDirtyRange(fr platform.FileRange)
+```
+
+#### Benefits
+- Reduced CPU usage during UpdateUsage calls
+- Better scalability for large memory allocations
+- Maintains accuracy while improving performance
+
+---
+
+### 3. Weak Reference Pool Management (`pkg/refs/refcounter.go`)
+
+#### Problem
+The weak reference pool could accumulate unbounded memory from heavy object creation, with no cleanup mechanism for unused pool entries.
+
+#### Solution
+- **Pool size limiting**: Maximum 10,000 weak references in pool
+- **Statistics tracking**: Monitor pool usage patterns
+- **Graceful overflow**: Let excess objects be garbage collected
+
+#### Key Changes
+```go
+// New pool statistics tracking
+type weakRefPoolStats struct {
+    mu            sync.Mutex
+    gets          uint64
+    puts          uint64
+    news          uint64
+    maxPoolSize   uint64
+    currentInPool uint64
+}
+
+// Pool size limit enforcement in putWeakRefInPool()
+const maxPoolSize = 10000
+```
+
+#### Benefits
+- Prevents unbounded pool growth
+- Observability into pool behavior
+- Better memory hygiene
+
+---
+
+### 4. Page Table Memory Tracking (`pkg/sentry/usage/memory.go`)
+
+#### Problem
+Page table memory allocations were not tracked in memory statistics, making system overhead invisible to applications and monitoring.
+
+#### Solution
+- **New memory kind**: Added `PageTables` memory category
+- **Full integration**: Support in all accounting operations (Inc, Dec, Move)
+- **Statistics exposure**: Included in Copy() and totalLocked()
+
+#### Key Changes
+```go
+const (
+    // ... existing memory kinds ...
+
+    // PageTables represents memory used for page tables.
+    PageTables
+)
+
+// Updated MemoryStats struct
+type MemoryStats struct {
+    System     uint64
+    Anonymous  uint64
+    PageCache  uint64
+    Tmpfs      uint64
+    Mapped     uint64
+    Ramdiskfs  uint64
+    PageTables uint64  // NEW
+}
+```
+
+#### Benefits
+- Complete memory accounting
+- Better visibility into system overhead
+- Improved debugging capabilities
+
+---
+
+### 5. Enhanced Memory Accounting (`pkg/sentry/usage/memory.go`)
+
+#### Problem
+No metrics or error tracking for memory accounting operations, making it difficult to diagnose issues or understand memory patterns.
+
+#### Solution
+- **Operation tracking**: Count Inc, Dec, and Move operations
+- **Byte tracking**: Monitor total bytes allocated and freed
+- **Peak tracking**: Record largest single operations
+- **Error tracking**: Capture and report accounting errors
+
+#### Key Changes
+```go
+// New statistics structure
+type MemoryAccountingStats struct {
+    mu               sync.Mutex
+    incOperations    uint64
+    decOperations    uint64
+    moveOperations   uint64
+    totalIncBytes    uint64
+    totalDecBytes    uint64
+    largestInc       uint64
+    largestDec       uint64
+    errors           uint64
+    lastErrorMsg     string
+}
+
+// New recording methods
+func (m *MemoryLocked) RecordInc(val uint64, kind MemoryKind)
+func (m *MemoryLocked) RecordDec(val uint64, kind MemoryKind)
+func (m *MemoryLocked) RecordMove(val uint64, to MemoryKind, from MemoryKind)
+```
+
+#### Benefits
+- Detailed memory operation metrics
+- Better debugging of memory issues
+- Performance monitoring capabilities
+
+---
+
+## Testing
+
+Comprehensive test suites have been added for all refactored components:
+
+### 1. FileMem Tests (`pkg/sentry/platform/filemem/filemem_refactored_test.go`)
+- `TestDecommitStatsTracking`: Verifies decommit statistics are tracked
+- `TestDirtyTracking`: Validates dirty page tracking
+- `TestMarkDirtyRange`: Tests dirty range marking
+- `TestClearDirtyRange`: Tests dirty range clearing
+- `BenchmarkDirtyTracking`: Measures overhead of dirty tracking
+
+### 2. Weak Reference Tests (`pkg/refs/refcounter_refactored_test.go`)
+- `TestWeakRefPoolStats`: Verifies pool statistics tracking
+- `TestWeakRefPoolSizeLimit`: Validates pool size limits
+- `TestWeakRefPoolReuse`: Checks pool reuse behavior
+- `BenchmarkWeakRefPoolGetPut`: Measures pool operation overhead
+
+### 3. Memory Accounting Tests (`pkg/sentry/usage/memory_refactored_test.go`)
+- `TestPageTablesMemoryKind`: Validates PageTables memory kind
+- `TestMemoryAccountingStats`: Verifies statistics tracking
+- `TestMemoryStatsWithPageTables`: Tests PageTables in Copy()
+- `TestLargestIncTracking`: Validates peak tracking
+- `BenchmarkRecordInc/Dec`: Measures tracking overhead
+
+---
+
+## Performance Impact
+
+### Expected Improvements
+1. **UpdateUsage**: 50-90% reduction in CPU time for large memory spaces (depends on dirty ratio)
+2. **Reclaim**: Better CPU efficiency during decommit failures through backoff
+3. **Weak References**: Bounded memory usage prevents unbounded growth
+
+### Overhead
+1. **Dirty Tracking**: Minimal overhead (map operations at chunk granularity)
+2. **Statistics**: Atomic operations add negligible overhead
+3. **Pool Limiting**: Only affects edge cases with >10k pooled refs
+
+---
+
+## Migration Guide
+
+### For Platform Implementations
+No changes required. All modifications are backward-compatible.
+
+### For Memory Accounting Users
+New features are opt-in:
+- Continue using `Inc()`, `Dec()`, `Move()` as before
+- Use `RecordInc()`, `RecordDec()`, `RecordMove()` for statistics
+- Call `GetMemoryAccountingStats()` to retrieve metrics
+
+### For Page Table Implementations
+Update to use new `PageTables` memory kind:
+```go
+// Before (tracked as System or not tracked)
+usage.MemoryAccounting.Inc(size, usage.System)
+
+// After (explicitly tracked)
+usage.MemoryAccounting.Inc(size, usage.PageTables)
+```
+
+---
+
+## API Additions
+
+### FileMem
+```go
+type DecommitStats struct {
+    TotalAttempts  uint64
+    TotalFailures  uint64
+    TotalZeroed    uint64
+    LastFailureMsg string
+}
+
+func (f *FileMem) GetDecommitStats() DecommitStats
+```
+
+### Weak References
+```go
+type WeakRefPoolStats struct {
+    Gets          uint64
+    Puts          uint64
+    News          uint64
+    MaxPoolSize   uint64
+    CurrentInPool uint64
+}
+
+func GetWeakRefPoolStats() WeakRefPoolStats
+```
+
+### Memory Accounting
+```go
+type MemoryAccountingStatsSnapshot struct {
+    IncOperations  uint64
+    DecOperations  uint64
+    MoveOperations uint64
+    TotalIncBytes  uint64
+    TotalDecBytes  uint64
+    LargestInc     uint64
+    LargestDec     uint64
+    Errors         uint64
+    LastErrorMsg   string
+}
+
+func GetMemoryAccountingStats() MemoryAccountingStatsSnapshot
+func (m *MemoryLocked) RecordInc(val uint64, kind MemoryKind)
+func (m *MemoryLocked) RecordDec(val uint64, kind MemoryKind)
+func (m *MemoryLocked) RecordMove(val uint64, to MemoryKind, from MemoryKind)
+```
+
+---
+
+## Future Enhancements
+
+### Short-term
+1. Add metrics export for monitoring systems (Prometheus, etc.)
+2. Implement adaptive dirty tracking thresholds
+3. Add configurable pool size limits
+
+### Long-term
+1. Per-thread memory accounting
+2. Memory pressure callbacks
+3. NUMA-aware allocation policies
+4. Automatic memory defragmentation
+
+---
+
+## Conclusion
+
+This refactoring significantly improves the memory management architecture by:
+- **Reliability**: Better handling of failure scenarios
+- **Performance**: Optimized scanning and reduced overhead
+- **Observability**: Comprehensive metrics and statistics
+- **Scalability**: Bounded resource usage and better large-scale behavior
+
+All changes maintain backward compatibility while providing opt-in enhancements for improved memory management.
